Program: Outlook
Title: 29/09/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00kb8dl
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 3 Oct 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, a Ugandan doctor tells us what it was like to be the only cancer specialist in a country with one of the highest cancer rates in the world. Dr Jackson Orem sees up to ten thousand patients a year. Also, why Angela Walters, who lives in the town of Joplin in the American state of Missouri, is spending so much time restoring photographs scattered far and wide by a tornado. And, Kuly, Manj and Surj Singh make up the band RDB. These three Sikh brothers from northern England are making it big in Bollywood with their film tracks. Show less